.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-IMPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-import \- Import dashboard JSON files through the Grafana API.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard import [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Import dashboard JSON files through the Grafana API.
.PP
Use this when you have a local export tree or provisioning tree and need to push dashboards back into Grafana, either live or as a dry run. This command consumes raw/ or provisioning/ inputs; it does not consume the Grafana UI prompt/ lane.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-import\-dir
source directory for raw or combined export input.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-format
choose raw or provisioning.
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id, \-\-use\-export\-org, \-\-only\-org\-id, \-\-create\-missing\-orgs
control cross\-org routing.
.TP
.B \-\-import\-folder\-uid
force a destination folder UID.
.TP
.B \-\-ensure\-folders, \-\-replace\-existing, \-\-update\-existing\-only
control import behavior.
.TP
.B \-\-require\-matching\-folder\-path, \-\-require\-matching\-export\-org, \-\-strict\-schema, \-\-target\-schema\-version
safety checks.
.TP
.B \-\-import\-message
revision message stored in Grafana.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive, \-\-dry\-run, \-\-table, \-\-json, \-\-output\-format, \-\-output\-columns, \-\-no\-header, \-\-progress, \-\-verbose
preview and reporting controls.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Import dashboard JSON files through the Grafana API.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard import --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --import-dir ./dashboards/raw --replace-existing
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
